post_text: Over the last week, we have continued to carefully consider the uncertainty facing our community, state, nation and world. With information the Governor has recently presented in her press conferences, Macomb County has the highest rate of cases per million in the Detroit Region with 97 cases per million people per day and a positivity rate of 7.3%. It has become clear that we need time to ensure our student and staff safety by reviewing and refining our safety protocol implementation prior to bringing students back for any in person learning. With all of this data and information, we have made the difficult decision to have ALL students start the 2020-21 school year in a Virtual (at home) Learning environment. We will continue to monitor the data from the Macomb County Health Department and recommend changes as the data allows. For more information please visit: http://fitz.k12.mi.us/return-to-learn/

Summer Central Enrollment opens July 6!

District residents interested in enrollment for the 2020-21 school year can now select an appointment date / time when completing the Registration Gateway process. If you are a district resident that completed the Registration Gateway process during the COVID-19 state mandated school closure, you will receive a phone call to set up an appointment date / time. You may also contact our summer Central Enrollment office beginning July 6.

If you do not reside within our district, please visit our School of Choice page for more info on how to apply.

May 21 at 9:06 PM ·

Many seniors submitted applications to be this year’s Student Commencement Speaker. The process involved a panel questionnaire, a taped audition of the first paragraph of the speech, and the submission of letters of recommendation from FHS staff. After reviewing many outstanding applications, we would like to announce and congratulate ISHAK AHMED for being chosen as this year’s student speaker.
His speech will be part of the graduation dvd! We are looking forward to it! Congratulations Ishak!

Fitzgerald High School
April 28 at 4:58 AM ·

Congratulations
to the following Breaking Traditions
Certificate of Recognition Winner!!
Shainah Wilson

Fitzgerald Public Schools is proud to announce that senior,
Shainah Wilson, was chosen to receive one of the 2020 Breaking Traditions Awards for her hard work and dedication in the Automotive Technology Program. Students chosen for these awards overcome perceived barriers to achieve success in career and technical educational programs that are nontraditional to their gender, which makes them role models to their peers who may be considering the same career path. Shainah has been recognized with a 2020 Certificate and Letter of Recognition from the Michigan Department of Education’s Career & Technical Education Department. Congratulations Shainah!!! We are extremely proud of you!

Students chosen for these awards overcome perceived barriers to achieve success in career and technical educational programs that are nontraditional to their gender, which makes them role models to their peers who may be considering the same career path. Shainah has been recognized with a 2020 Certificate and Letter of Recognition from the Michigan Department of Education’s Career & Technical Education Department. Congratulations Shainah!!! We are extremely proud of you!
